FBIS4-1081 "drafr077_c_94024" FBIS-AFR-94-077 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Police Strike Averted Over Pay Parity After Election Police Strike Averted Over Pay Parity After Election MB2104073894 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0500 GMT 21 Apr 94 MB2104073894 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The threat of a countrywide police strike has been averted by a Transitional Executive Council agreement in principle on pay parity between all police forces in the country after the election. However, the South African Police Union is still negotiating with the TEC for a R61.50 [rand] daily election allowance in addition to a R21.50 a day police allowance.
